Avusa Falls For a Second Day After Capitau Offers $395 Million For Company

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-03-30T08:24:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/avusa-falls-for-a-second-day-after-capitau-offers-395-million-for-company.html
Avusa Ltd. (AVU) , which runs a publishing
venture with Pearson Plc in  South Africa , declined for a second
day after Capitau Holdings Ltd., a buyout firm, offered to buy
the company for 2.7 billion rand.  The stock declined 35 cents, or 1.5 percent, to 24.45 rand
by 10:23 a.m. in Johannesburg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sikonathi Mantshantsha in Johannesburg at 
